@muveluvr says:"if you all think they make movies ONLY FOR ENTERTAINMENT like stated you are so like ostriches with your heads in the sand if you don't think they are biased and aimed at helping you to form an opinion one way or the other."

OMG here's another live one who needs to read a book for once in his life. No. It's called the old debate between art imitating life, or life imitating art. The opinions are already formed moron...people come along to make movies that conform to the opinion. That's why you have movies like this, and then you have movies like "V for Vendetta". For that matter that's also why you have "liberal" or "conservative" papers -- because they understand their audience. The moment they write something that doesn't conform with what their audience wants to hear is the moment they lose business.

You tards who think the themes of these movies are all decided in some kind of "star chamber" somewhere are pathetic. I'd be surprised if you can even figure out how to tie your own shoes every day.
